      • onBookEvent

        public okhttp3.WebSocket onBookEvent​(List<String> symbols,
                                     Integer depth,
                                     PoloApiCallback<BookEvent> callback)
        Book Channel: Continuous feed of order book data containing asks and bids with default/provided depth.
        Parameters:
        symbols - symbol name
        depth - Default depth is 5. Valid depths are 5, 10, or 20
        callback - callback to handle book events
        Example:
          publicWebsocket.onBookEvent(List.of("ETH_USDT"), 10, new PoloLoggingCallback<>());

      • onBookLv2Event

        public okhttp3.WebSocket onBookLv2Event​(List<String> symbols,
                                        PoloApiCallback<BookLv2Event> callback)
        Book Level 2 Channel: Receive a snapshot of the full 20 level order book. Then, continuously in realtime receive an updated order book when the first 20 levels change.
        Parameters:
        symbols - symbol name
        callback - callback to handle book level 2 events
        Example:
          publicWebsocket.onBookLv2Event(List.of("BTC_USDT","ETH_USDT"), new PoloLoggingCallback<>());
